Biography
Born out of the molten crust of a distant moon, two luminous beings found solace in the velveteen sweeps of analog filters. Jon Stone and Hill Baker formed Neptune Massive subconsciously in 1983, and began playing in 2007. The debut album was born on 10/8/12 with the surgical assistance of Tim Green at Louder Studios. Within you'll find: analog soundscapes, soaring synthesizers, precision tuned instruments, hunchback dreams, shifting meters, and a lifelong friend.

"...with subtle notes of mu-lan, and wood sided panels to boot... this is... an instant classic."
- Apollo Wheatcream
